Elements are attributes possessed by every Pal and by every Active Skill, affecting its abilities in battle. Every Pal has at least one Element (sometimes two), and every Active Skill has one Element. Moves with Elements that are strong against the target Pal's element will deal more damage, and moves with Elements that are weak against the target Pal's element will deal less damage. Elements are one of the core gameplay mechanics of Palworld, being an innate part of a Pal that affects their behaviour and how they function in certain situations, such as in battle. Each Pal has either one or two elements. For example, Dazzi is a Pal with just the Electric element, while  Relaxaurus is a Pal that has both the Dragon and Water elements.

{Neutral is one of 9 elements. Neutral is weak to Dark and does not have a strength against any other element.}

{Fire is one of 9 elements. Fire is strong against Ice and Grass, and is weak to Water. Fire-element Pals are able to heat campfires, cooking pots and furnaces with  Kindling. Fire Pals are immune to the Burn and Ivy-Covered status effects.}

{Water is one of 9 elements. Water is strong against Fire and weak to Electric. Water-element Pals are able to water farms and other devices. Water Pals are immune to the Soak status effect.}

{Grass is one of 9 elements. Grass is strong against Ground and weak to Fire. Grass Pals are immune to the Ivy-Covered and Muddy status effects.}

{Electric is one of 9 elements. Electric is strong against Water and is weak to Ground. Electric-element Pals are able to generate electricity to power generators. Electric Pals are immune to the Electrify status effect.}

{Ice is one of 9 elements. Ice is strong against Dragon and is weak to Fire. Ice-type skills have a chance to freeze a target in a block of ice. Ice-element Pals are able to cool refrigerators with the Cooling Work Suitability. Ice Pals are immune to the Freeze status effect.}

{Ground is one of 9 elements. Ground is strong against Electric and weak to Grass. Ground Pals are immune to the Electrify and Muddy status effects.}

{Dark is one of 9 elements. Pals of this elemental type are usually nocturnal; meaning they naturally spawn during the night, do not need to sleep and will continue to work in bases day and night (exceptions to this rule exist, such as Lovander who is a Neutral type but nocturnal). As a result, this makes this type more susceptible to Sanity drain. Pals working at the player's base with the Dark element will keep working during the night, whilst others go to sleep, and so they don't need beds unless they're overworked. As for the current version of the game, they do not go to sleep during the day time,leaving them prone to being overworked. Unlike other elements, which resist the element they're strong against, Dark does not resist Neutral. Dark Pals are immune to the Blind status effect.}

{Dragon is one of 9 elements. Dragon is strong against Dark and is weak to Ice.}

