Pal Spheres are items used to capture Pals in Palworld. Pal spheres can be found in the wild, dropped from enemies, dug up from the Ranch, or crafted. Pal spheres spawn in random locations on the ground or in chests. The type of sphere will depend on the location: higher level areas will give better spheres. Some hostile NPCs will drop pal spheres. These NPCs may show up during Raids. To craft a pal sphere, it must first be unlocked in the Technology window. Different pal spheres require different buildings to craft them in. There are different types of pal spheres with different strengths. To use a pal sphere, the player must have them in their inventory. Throwing pal spheres does not consume stamina. Higher level pals are more difficult to catch, and thus are more easily caught with a better type of sphere. You can catch Pals and Alpha bosses and dungeon bosses with it. Although it is considered inhumane, you can also catch humans with it. If you aim at a Pal from behind, you will get a back bonus and get a higher catch chance. Pal spheres cannot be thrown while gliding, but can be while flying or mounted, crouched or sliding, falling, or aiming with a loaded bow.

{Pal Sphere: A Pal Sphere is the lowest tier of Pal Spheres available to newcomers on Palpagos Islands. It is the most basic of the Pal Spheres, which are items used to capture and store Pals. It is recommended to use on low level Pals. The color of this sphere is blue.}

{Mega Sphere: Mega Sphere is an improved version of Pal Sphere. An item that captures Pals when thrown. Its capabilities have been improved, allowing it to catch a wider range of Pals. The color of this sphere is green.}

{Giga Sphere: Giga Sphere is an improved version of Mega Sphere. A sphere that captures Pals when thrown. Able to capture moderately powerful Pals. The color of this sphere is golden yellow.}

{Hyper Sphere: Hyper Sphere is an improved version of Giga Sphere. A sphere that captures Pals when thrown. Able to capture very powerful Pals. The color of this sphere is scarlet red.}

{Ultra Sphere: Ultra Sphere is an improved version of Hyper Sphere. A sphere that captures Pals when thrown. With powerful abilities, not many Pals are able to escape it. The color of this sphere is dark pink.}

{Legendary Sphere: Ultra Sphere is an improved version of Hyper Sphere. A sphere that captures Pals when thrown. It has extremely powerful capturing capabilities, leaving almost no Pal able to escape. The color of this sphere is purple.}

{Ultimate Sphere: Ultimate Sphere is an improved version of Legendary Sphere. A sphere that captures Pals when thrown. Almost no Pals can escape its flawless design. The color of this sphere is dark with white dots like the night sky with the addition of a purple and blue filter.}

5.content:
Lamball is a Neutral elemental Pal. A walk up a hill tends to end with this Pal tumbling back down. This causes it to become dizzy and unable to move, making it easy to capture and kill. As a result, this Pal has tumbled down to the very bottom of the food chain itself. Lamball, as their name suggests, is a spherical pal resembling a lamb. They are bipedal and have short stubby arms and legs and shiny golden eyes. The body and long ears of Lamball are a greyish brown with white wool enveloping their body. On the top of a Lamball's head features two small orange horns. They have two gold gems on their chest similar to buttons which, combined with their wool, give off the appearance of a parka. Lamballs are curious of the Player when they approach it. If attacked, they will attack back with its signature Roly Poly Active Skill.

{Partner Skill: Fluffy Shield - When activated, equips to the player and becomes a shield. Sometimes drops Wool when assigned to ranch.}

{Work Suitability: Handiwork 1, Transporting 1, Farming 1}

{Possible Drops: Normal 1-3 Wool, 1 Lamball Mutton}

{Farming Produce: Wool}

6.content:
Cattiva is a Neutral element Pal. At a glance it appears full of confidence, but it is in fact weak and cowardly. Being toyed with by a Cattiva is in many ways the greatest of disgraces. Cattiva is a pal that resembles a small bipedal pink cat. It has four thick whiskers on its face with two on each side. Cattiva's forehead sports an exaggerated tuft of fur. Cattiva has a tail that is short and curly in appearance. The ears of Cattiva are triangular and inside of its ears are black. Cattiva has an underbelly that is cream. Cattiva often is seen in a confident expression and has bright blue eyes. When its mouth is open, two fangs can be seen inside Cattiva's mouth. In the wild this Pal will run away if it spots the player. While working at the player's base this Pal tends to slack off a lot, take breaks frequently, and sometimes when angry will even go to bed in the middle of the day.

{Partner Skill: Cat Helper - While in team, Cattiva helps carry supplies, increasing the player's max carrying capacity by 50. With multiple Cattiva, it stacks.}

{Passive Skill: Coward - Cattiva will always have this Passive Skill after being captured.}

{Work Suitability: Handiwork 1, Transporting 1, Gathering 1, Mining 1}

{Possible Drops: Red Berries}

7.content:
Chikipi is a  Neutral element Pal. Extremely weak and far too delicious. It is one of the weakest Pals alongside Lamball. No matter how many are hunted, they just keep appearing. Chikipi is a pal resembling a white chicken. Its body is vaguely egg-shaped and it has grey oval eyes. The beak of Chikipi is yellow and features a red wattle. The feet of Chikipi are orange with two clawed toes in the front and one toe at the back of the foot. The top of a Chikipi's head has a large comb that is red just like its waddle. Wild Chikipi may sporadically lay eggs on the ground, which can be picked up by the player. This Pal retaliates only when attacked, though neighboring Chikipi will become aggressive upon witnessing another Chikipi being harmed by the player.

{Partner Skill: Egg Layer - Sometimes lays eggs when assigned to Ranch.}

{Work Suitability: Gathering 1, Farming 1}

{Possible Drops: Egg, Chikipi Poultry}

{Farming Produce: Egg}

8.content:
Lifmunk is a Grass element Pal. Intelligent as a five to seven-year-old human child. It makes a wonderful partner, but there have been more than a few cases where they've killed their master after learning to use weapons. Lifmunk is a pal taking on the appearance of rodents such as squirrels and chipmunks. Their body primarily consists of a light greenish yellow color. The tail of Lifmunk is large and bushy and is tipped with white. Their ears, whiskers and collar all take on the appearance of green leaves with the right ear having a distinct notch giving the appearance of a bitten leaf. Their shiny eyes are a bright red-orange, and they have a large gem on their forehead to match. Underneath their collar, there can be seen two red berries attached to their chest, possibly resembling cherries. Wild Lifmunk will often run away from the player upon sight. When attacked, it keeps running away.

{Partner Skill: Lifmunk Recoil - When activated, leaps onto player's head and uses a submachine gun to follows up player attacks. (Requires Lifmunk's Submachine Gun)}

{Work Suitability: Planting 1, Handiwork 1, Lumbering 1, Medicine 1, Production 1, Gathering 1}

{Possible Drops: Berry Seeds, Low Grade Medical Supplies}

9.content:
Foxparks is a Fire element Pal. It is unskilled at controlling fire from the moment it is born and tends to choke on the flames it breathes unintentionally. Foxparks sneezes are one of the leading causes of forest fires. Foxparks is a firey fox pal that is a bright red-orange bearing resemblance to a red fox. Its ears are long with the insides being tan and the ends of the ears are tipped in black. It has eyebrows that are a lighter shade of yellow. On each side of Foxsparks' face, messy tufts of fur are visible. The stomach of Foxsparks like the inside of its ears are tan. It has a large bushy tail that like its ears, is tipped with a black pattern. A prominent feature on Foxsparks is being engulfed with flames that cover over its legs and the tip of its tail. The eyes of Foxparks come a crimson red color. This Pal is a fairly timid creature that will usually flee away upon sighting a player. It is usually found travelling alone or in pairs.

{Partner Skill: Huggy Fire - When activated, equips to the player and transform into a flamethrower. (Requires Foxparks's Harness)}

{Work Suitability: Kindling 1}

{Possible Drops: Leather, Flame Organ}

10.content:
Fuack is a Water element Pal. Using its own body water, this Pal can create waves anywhere. It body surfs when in a hurry, but the resulting speed often ends in a fatal collision. Fuack appears like a blue, bipedal platypus with a yellow duck bill and two strange tufts sticking out on its head resembling pigtails. It has a white frill around its neck, split up into several bead-like segments. It also has a beaver or platypus tail, which is a slightly different shade of blue than the rest of its body. This Pal can be found roaming around bodies of water and inland, it may run away from the player. Like most Pals, wild Fuack will retaliate when attacked.

{Partner Skill: Surfing Slam - When activated, Fuack body surfs towards an enemy and slams into them.}

{Work Suitability: Handiwork 1, Transporting 1, Watering 1}

{Possible Drops: Leather, Pal Fluids}

